# file-naming.mdc
# Purpose: Enforce consistent file naming across project
# Scope: all file types (source, test, debug, notebooks, docs, exports)

All files in the project must follow consistent and descriptive naming conventions to ensure discoverability, clarity, and traceability across the codebase.

GENERAL_CONVENTIONS:
  - Use snake_case for all Python files: lowercase letters with underscores.
  - Filenames must reflect the purpose or main component of the file.
  - Avoid generic names like test.py, data.py, utils.py unless scoped in clearly named folders.

TEST_FILES:
  - Pattern: test_<NN>_<module>[_<purpose>].py
    • NN = two-digit index (00–99) for natural order
    • module = name of the source file tested (without .py)
    • purpose = optional tag for variant or special case
  - All test files must live under the tests/ folder.
  - Example: test_01_normalization_strategy.py

DEBUG_FILES:
  - Pattern: debug_<pkg>_<module>[_<experiment>].py
    • pkg = prefix formed by concatenating the first 3 letters of each word in the folder name
      - neural_network/ → neu_net
      - data_preprocessing/ → dat_pre
      - assemble_methods/ → ass_met
      - metrics/ → met
      - utils/ → uti
    • module = name of the file being debugged (omit .py)
    • experiment = optional short slug for the debug purpose
  - All debug files must live under debug/ and must be excluded via .gitignore.
  - Examples:
    • debug_neu_net_pipeline_gradient_check.py
    • debug_dat_pre_normalization_new_scaler.py
    • debug_ass_met_voting_ensemble_robustness.py
    • debug_met_masked_prediction_unknown_index.py
    • debug_uti_example_plot_usage.py

NOTEBOOKS:
  - Pattern: <NN>_<topic>[_<variant>].ipynb
    • NN = optional numeric prefix for order
    • topic = what the notebook focuses on
    • variant = optional slug
  - Example: 01_feature_engineering_exploration.ipynb

DOCUMENTATION:
  - Pattern: <NN>_<module>[_<scope>].md
    • NN = Optional numeric prefix for visual ordering (00–99)
    • module = Name of the Python file being documented (omit .py)
    • scope = Optional detail about the document's focus (e.g. workflow, params, math)

OUTPUTS_AND_EXPORTS:
  - All temporary or generated files must include a tag identifying their source.
  - Prefer patterns like: <model_name>_predictions.csv, logs_<timestamp>.txt
  - If versioned output is needed, suffix with _v<major>_<minor>

CONFIGURATION:
  - YAML or JSON config files should clearly describe their target system or purpose.
  - Examples: model_config.yaml, ui_settings.json
